<div class="mt-5">
<div class="container p-4 my-4">
<h1 class="text-center fw-bold">Leukemia: A Complete Overview</h1>
<p class="text-center text-muted">Understanding leukemia, its types, symptoms, and treatment options.</p>

<!-- Introduction Section -->
<div class="card p-4 my-4">
    <h2><i class="bi bi-book"></i> What is Leukemia?</h2>
    <p>Leukemia is a type of blood cancer that originates in the bone marrow, affecting white blood cells. It disrupts normal blood production and weakens the immune system.</p>
</div>


<!-- Types of Leukemia -->
<div class="card p-4 my-4">
    <h2><i class="bi bi-list-ul"></i> Types of Leukemia</h2>
    <ul class="list-group">
        <li class="list-group-item"><b>Acute Lymphoblastic Leukemia (ALL)</b> - Common in children, rapid progression.</li>
        <li class="list-group-item"><b>Acute Myeloid Leukemia (AML)</b> - Affects older adults, fast-growing.</li>
        <li class="list-group-item"><b>Chronic Lymphocytic Leukemia (CLL)</b> - Slow-growing, common in elderly.</li>
        <li class="list-group-item"><b>Chronic Myeloid Leukemia (CML)</b> - Linked to genetic mutations, progresses over time.</li>
    </ul>
</div>

<!-- Symptoms -->
<div class="card p-4 my-4">
    <h2><i class="bi bi-exclamation-triangle"></i> Symptoms</h2>
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <ul class="list-group">
                <li class="list-group-item">Fatigue and weakness</li>
                <li class="list-group-item">Unexplained weight loss</li>
                <li class="list-group-item">Frequent infections</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <ul class="list-group">
                <li class="list-group-item">Easy bruising or bleeding</li>
                <li class="list-group-item">Swollen lymph nodes, fever, night sweats</li>
                <li class="list-group-item">Bone pain or tenderness</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

    <!-- Preventive Measures -->
    <div class="card p-4 my-4">
        <h2><i class="bi bi-shield-check"></i> Preventive Measures</h2>
        <p>While leukemia cannot always be prevented, certain lifestyle changes can help reduce the risk.</p>
        <ul class="list-group">
            <li class="list-group-item"><b>Avoid Smoking:</b> Tobacco smoke contains harmful chemicals linked to leukemia.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item"><b>Limit Exposure to Radiation & Chemicals:</b> Reduce exposure to benzene and pesticides.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item"><b>Healthy Diet:</b> Eat a balanced diet rich in fruits, vegetables, and whole grains.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item"><b>Regular Exercise:</b> Staying active boosts overall health and immune function.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item"><b>Manage Stress:</b> Chronic stress can weaken immunity; practice relaxation techniques.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item"><b>Routine Health Checkups:</b> Early detection can improve outcomes if leukemia develops.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>


<!-- Diagnosis -->
<div class="card p-4 my-4">
    <h2><i class="bi bi-clipboard-check"></i> Diagnosis</h2>
    <ul class="list-group">
        <li class="list-group-item"><b>Blood Tests:</b> Detects abnormal white blood cells.</li>
        <li class="list-group-item"><b>Bone Marrow Biopsy:</b> Examines bone marrow samples.</li>
        <li class="list-group-item"><b>Genetic Testing:</b> Identifies mutations related to leukemia.</li>
    </ul>
</div>

<!-- Treatment Options -->
<div class="card p-4 my-4">
    <h2><i class="bi bi-capsule"></i> Treatment Options</h2>
    <ul class="list-group">
        <li class="list-group-item"><b>Chemotherapy:</b> Drugs to kill cancer cells.</li>
        <li class="list-group-item"><b>Radiation Therapy:</b> High-energy rays to target leukemia cells.</li>
        <li class="list-group-item"><b>Bone Marrow Transplant:</b> Replaces diseased bone marrow with healthy cells.</li>
        <li class="list-group-item"><b>Targeted Therapy & Immunotherapy:</b> Attacks leukemia cells while preserving normal cells.</li>
    </ul>
</div>

<!-- FAQs -->
<div class="card p-4 my-4">
    <h2><i class="bi bi-question-circle"></i> FAQs</h2>
    <div class="accordion" id="faqAccordion">
        <div class="accordion-item">
            <h2 class="accordion-header">
                <button class="accordion-button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq1">
                    Can leukemia be cured?
                </button>
            </h2>
            <div id="faq1" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                    Some types, like childhood ALL, have high cure rates. Others can be managed with long-term treatment.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="accordion-item">
            <h2 class="accordion-header">
                <button class="accordion-button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq2">
                    Is leukemia always hereditary?
                </button>
            </h2>
            <div id="faq2" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                    No, while genetics play a role, most cases are not inherited.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        

        <div class="accordion-item">
            <h2 class="accordion-header">
                <button class="accordion-button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq3">
                    Does early detection improve outcomes?
                </button>
            </h2>
            <div id="faq3" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                    Yes! Early diagnosis and treatment significantly improve survival rates.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

